description:
`<>` indicates a required argument
`[]` indicates the argument is optional
`...` it indicates multiple of the same type of argument
You do not include these characters in the command.

fields.name: ⠀
fields.value:
**Customize your server's prefix**
`@JirosCal#7363 prefix <new_prefix>`
`@JirosCal#7363 prefix`

**Set your server's default event invite link**
`@JirosCal#7363 link <invite_link>`
`@JirosCal#7363 link`
link should never expire

**Specify where events from followed servers get displayed**
`@JirosCal#7363 here`

**Follow other servers' events**
`@JirosCal#7363 [un]follow <all/server_name>`
`@JirosCal#7363 following`
can be used in dm's as well

**See upcoming races**
`@JirosCal#7363 calendar [all/following]`
defaults to following

**Create, edit, and delete events**
`@JirosCal#7363 event create`
~~`@JirosCal#7363 event edit/delete <event_id>`~~

"event" aliases: 
`playlist`, `pl`
`race`, `one-off`, `oneoff`
`championship`, `league`
`time-trial`, `timetrial`, `tt`

**Whitelist other hosts**
`@JirosCal#7363 whitelist @user`
must be a whitelisted host to use this command
